{
  "stem": "21812.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The one, the one incident that I'll always remember was, we had a gym teacher that was in gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I, I didn't know that he was a Nazi.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He, he was.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And as soon as-- when-- just before the Nazis actually came in legally, he already wore a swastika button, as a lot of others did.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- nut he took us on an outing, a day's outing, and he got lost.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We went into the Alps, into the forerunners of the Alps, and he got lost.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And then, of course, for him that was a very unpleasant experience.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "After all, he considered himself a very proper person and a knowledgeable person, and so on and so forth.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So-- and we had to do a lot of hiking.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We had-- in order to get back, we had probably hiked twice as much as we should have.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And it was pretty strenuous.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so at the end of the day, he remarked, well, even in this school, I can see that there are-- that there are people who can take that kind of strenuous exercise, meaning that the Jews can also-- [LAUGHS] --manage to hike those distances.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I always remember that because it was really the first time that a teacher came out with that kind of a remark.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 14.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it wasn't-- as I said, we were isolated in that school, really.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I'm, I'm sure pupils have been in-- children who had been in different districts, which were, you know, maybe, mostly Gentile or had a different mixture of Jews and Gentile would have heard that many times before.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But for us, as I said, you know, we were really isolated in that respect.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And on the other hand, anti-Semitism was all around us.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
